% 1. 学習データの準備
numSamples = 100;
numInputs = 3;
numOutputs = 2;
P = rand(numInputs, numSamples);
T = rand(numOutputs, numSamples) * 10;

% 2. ネットワークの作成
hiddenLayerSize = 10;
net = fitnet(hiddenLayerSize);

% 3. ネットワークの学習
[net, tr] = train(net, P, T);

% 4. 推論（予測）
numNewSamples = 5;
P_new = rand(numInputs, numNewSamples);
Y_pred = net(P_new);
disp(Y_pred);

I have some legacy matlab neural network training scripts and want to modernize them, can you do that for me? Here's the first script:

rng(21)
[X,T] = simpleseries_dataset;
Xnew = X(81:100);
Tnew = T(81:100);
X = X(1:80);
T = T(1:80);

net = narxnet(0:2,1:2,11);
[Xs,Xi,Ai,Ts] = preparets(net,X,{},T);
net = train(net,Xs,Ts,Xi,Ai);

netc = closeloop(net);
[Xs,Xi,Ai,Ts] = preparets(netc, X(end-2:end), {}, T(end-2:end));
y2 = netc(Xnew, Xi, Ai);
y2 = seq2con(y2);
y2 = y2{1};

Tnew = seq2con(Tnew);
Tnew = Tnew{1};
T = seq2con(T);
T = T{1};

figure
plot(1:100,[T,Tnew],'b-o',1:100,[T,y2],'r--*')
legend({'Reference';'Simulation (From 81 - 100)'})
grid on

